file=Product/ux/operational/skill/ux-skill-routing.md · u—s:ux — Skill Routing Map=Non-leader: law (the Evidence Gate — ux is the evidence supply) + this routing decide WHICH skill WHEN.\n\n```\nresearch request ─► research-repository (QUERY FIRST) ─verdict─► ANSWERED (cite, no study) \| STALE (re-validate) \| GAP\n│\nGAP ─► study-design (protocol/method/sample/consent) ─► run\n│ raw data\nsynthesis-discipline (claims + confidence + trace)\n│ filed\nresearch-repository (tagged, cited-by)\nsupport/reviews/NPS ─► voice-of-customer-intake (tag, pattern) ─► repo (directional) \| GAP flag ─► study-design\n```\n\nHandoffs out: spec (repo IDs = PRD evidence; GAP-driven findings) \· loom (assumption checks, qualitative why) \· metric (behavioral magnitude is metric's; co-cited) \· Client Success/future (read-only intake boundary) \· Behavioral Science/future (bias theory dependency, flagged not inlined) \· anneal (a shipped miss traced to a stale/over-confident finding → skill lesson).\nPrecedence: query-first before any study; confidence flag rides every claim; intake is read-only on the support pipeline.\n